I ordered drunken noodles, calamari, chicken screw. Drunken noodles: very very dry, no flavors and extremely spicy, like I like spicy food but this was so spicy my lips and tongue were red and swollen. Calamari: dry and soggy, do not recommend for delivery Chicken screw: not even sure if it was chicken, the texture was a bit off for chicken but it’s taste pretty good and the peanut sauce went great with it. Sadly will not be ordering from here again.
Lunch specials are a must, especially love their soup that comes with the entree. I'm all about the chicken basil, never disappoints!

Nice neighborhood spot. Decent Thai food. All the good elements, fairly priced. You can always gauge a restaurant by its tum yum soup, it was very good. I got the soup, fried rice and shrimp rolls. Good stuff. The staff was friendly and professional. The establishment is adhering social distancing/ COVID regulations. Good local restaurant that is trying their best during this crazy time.

This place is awesome! We ordered through delivery.com and it said it would be ready in 40 minutes which was perfect timing! We picked up dinner and the staff was so nice! The drunken noodles were absolutely delicious along with the pineapple chicken fried rice. My boyfriend ordered the shrimp and chicken with vegetables and peanut sauce which he said had so many fresh vegetables it was amazing. The food was cooked and prepared so well and full of flavor. Highly recommend!!

Will definitely return here many times! We ordered the chicken nuggets- which tasted EXACTLY like mcdonald's nuggets! The orange chicken with a side of broccoli and kale- which was absolutely delicious. The sauce tasted very similar to the orange chicken from panda express and the chicken texture was very realistic! We also ordered the spicy ramen - and thanks to a yelp review i read i ordered the spicy sauce on the side which made it perfect! it was a perfect (very large) portion of perfect noodles and such a yummy broth! The restaurants environment was great. nicely decorated and not too crowded. The staff was nice and very helpful! The location of the restaurant was also very good! 10/10 !

Golden Thai have singlehandedly gotten me through this pandemic. They are efficient and the food is outstanding. At this point I have had the pleasure to try all of their curries and each one is better than the next. I highly recommend helping them out and placing your order. If my review doesn’t have you convinced I am attaching photos of their delicious meals. The sauce on the ribs is going to make you wish you had bought a second order. Curry is always smooth and has a lovely kick but never super spicy. There are a few fried appetizers that might be a little too greasy but overall they are very good. I’m looking forward to normalcy when I can visit them in person because the decor of the restaurant looks very nice too.
For those concerned about Covid, kitchen staff wearing their mask under their chins.

Ordered around 8pm and said it would be delivered by 9. Called at 910 and they said food will be here shortly. Called again at 9:45 and no one picked up. Called again at 10pm and NO ONE PICKED UP AGAIN. Finally got my food at 1010.

I rarely leave reviews but feel compelled to do so to balance out the negative ones, which seem so misplaced in a literal pandemic in which the existence of the restaurant industry is under threat.  That being said, I love golden thai. Reasonably priced, and one of the quickest delivery options in the area. I got the pad see ew with squid and my girlfriend got the drunk noodles with chicken. It came hot and fresh and was exactly what the both of us were craving. We also got the mango with sticky rice and it was one of the best renditions of that dish I’ve ever tried. Highly recommend if you’re in the area and looking for quick, satisfying takeout.

Ummm. The negative reviews for this restaurant are very accurate. The pad Thai had a weird sweet and sour taste, pink color and strange smell. The duck rolls were tasteless, aside from the overwhelming oil I noticed as I took my one and only bite. Sigh. Discarded much of the meal. I felt like I was forcing myself to eat it so eventually I had to just stop. I thought Thai was a sure bet but I was very underwhelmed.
this was the worst thai food i ever had. disgusting. worse than fast-food chinese.

I demonstrated to them that my card had been charged, making no attempt to amend the situation and the inconvenience they had caused me, told me to file a claim with my bank, causing me further inconvenience and wasting more of my time. TL;DR Golden Thai is excellent, high quality Thai and a cool atmosphere.  I came for lunch and tried the spicy fried rice and some fried tofu and it was awesome. The flavors were on point, dry sweat Thai heat broken by bright crisp veggies and the tufo was crispy without being dry. The atmosphere inside is small but well laid-out with a very Brooklynish vibe.  I've been a Bushwick resident for 8 years and Golden Thai is our neighborhood's answer to the likes of Williamsburg Thai; excellent Thai food, at a good price and in a cool setting. I no longer have to choose between my love of Thai food and my hatred of the L train. This is the restaurant the neighborhood needed!
